cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper presents a system for robot motion generation using deep learning and bilateral teleoperation. The focus is on the application of the system for robotic scooping tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques such as Deep Convolutional Auto-Encoders (DCAE) and Recurrent Neural Network with Long Short-Term Memory units (LSTM-RNN), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of visual images in the deep learning software also suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the adaptivity of the system, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also discusses the human-robot interaction aspect of the system, which suggests that it could belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
